data.title: Gunston School: Gunston Weekly
data.text:
Still looking for something to do this summer? Check out www.SummerProgramFinder.com, the Enrichment Program tab in Naviance (under the College tab), or in the document "Summer Programs by Subject Area".

Scholarship Opportunities:

Queen Anne's County Historical Society Scholarship: The Queen Anne’s County Historical Society is offering a $500 one-year scholarship to a graduating high school senior who is a current Queen Anne’s County resident and plans to attend a four-year college. To be eligible the applicant must: Be a resident of Queen Anne’s County for at least ten years, have a 3.0 GPA or higher; have an interest in history; and have performed community service in the County. Applications may be obtained from Ms. Margosian. Students will need to submit recommendation, transcript, and a 1-page essay on the importance of preserving the heritage of Queen Anne’s County by APRIL 30, 2015.

Cancer Comfort Angels Scholarship: CCA is providing a $1,000 scholarship (non-renewable) to a high school senior in good standing whose life has been affected by cancer, or who has made a difference in someone’s life who is fighting cancer. Applications may be obtained from Ms. Margosian, at their website (www.cancercomfortangels.org), or requested by email (cancercomfortangels@gmail.com). Applications should be mailed to: Cancer Comfort Angels, P. O. Box 253, Chester, MD 21619. DUE APRIL 30, 2015

JUNIORS:

Don't forget that there are a lot of ways to help you study for the SAT and ACT! Use the PrepMe program on Naviance, go to www.number2.com, or use the booklets you got in College 101.

Test dates:

SAT: March 14 (register by February 13), May 2 (register by April 6), and June 6. ** This is graduation day and is the ends of finals. I strongly encourage students NOT to register for the June test! http://sat.collegeboard.org/register

ACT: April 18 (register by March 13) and June 13 (register by May 8). http://www.actstudent.org/regist/

Juniors who need to take the TOEFL: I encourage you to take this before you leave for summer vacation! Please talk to Ms. Margosian or Ms. Vooris about this if you have questions.
